column1: Ryan Wiezorek sworn.  Direct by Attorney Linda Coleman:  Witness does maintenance for Bayfield Co. Housing  since 1/31/20. Describes dutes.  Maintains Defendant's bldg. in Iron River, Bayfield Co. 2x/wk. min. - 1 apt. in multi unit compound.  Yard 30 ft wide x 50 ft. long.  Witnessed dog feces in DE's yard. Dog tied up.
Exhibit #1 -Photos of dog feces on sidewalk at DE's unit.
Exhibit #2 - Photos at DE's unit.  Sees dog chain at unit everytime there and dog feces - multiple piles.   Exhibits #1 &amp
Exhibit #3 - Photo at DE unit.  Admitted and recieved.  Grass -  holes in multiple spots.  Witnessed dog digging at DE's unit.
Exhibit #4 - Photo of area in front of DE unit.  Other yards in area in good shape.  This area at DE unit disturbed.  Exhibit #4 - admitted and received.
Exhibit #5 - 3 photos at DE's unit on 6/11/21 - dirt dug and on sidewalk.  Exhibit - admitted and received.
Exhibit #6 - Photo from video.  Dog on chain w/o DE in front of DE unit 6/17/21.  Exhibit admitted and received.
Exhibit #7 - Photo from 6/29/21.  Destroyed yard in front of DE unit where chain extends.  Exhibit admitted and received.  Makeshift fence put in and now can't mow there.

Exhibit #8 - 2 photos - stakes with wire - assumes installed by DE, enclosed 6 ft. x 14 ft. area where chain extends.  Dirt where grass should be and dog feces.  Exhibit admitted and received.  Housing Dept. policy - dog cannot be tied outside.
Exhibit #9 - Photo 5/14/21 - chain wrapped around post and damage to wood railing - groove.  Exhibit admitted and received.
Exhibit #10 - Photo 5/26/21 - of Unit # and chain.  Exhibit admitted and received.  Witness usually at DE's unit after 9:00 AM.  He performs inspections for Housing.
Exhibit #11 -  Photo of porch area 6/3/21.    Exhibit #12 - Note - "No Inspection"  posted at DE's unit.  Exhibits #11 and #12 admitted and received.

Cross by Kathleen McBrair:  Witness states drainage pipe may have been installed prior to his hire in 1/2020.  6" x 12' where pipe is.  No major damage where pipe is installed.  Some grass missing.   Not aware that DE watches dog from window.  Grass reseeded needs to grow before mowing.  Age of posts unknown - paint won't repair damage - grooves in wood.  He clears sidewalks/ paths of snow in winter.

Redirect by Attorney Linda Coleman:  Did not witness DE watching dog from house.  Drainage pipe - he not present when buried.  Exhibit #4 - describes where pipe would be .  Exhibit #5 - 6/11/21 - areas not where pipe buried.
Recross by Kathleen McBrair:  Has not seen end of drainage pipe showing on lawn.
Tamara Deragon sworn in.  Direct by Attorney Linda Coleman:  She executive director of City of Washburn Bayfield Co. Housing Development.  Knows DE.  Her unit is at Columbia Monor #1 in Iron River.
Exhibit #13 - Residential Lease with DE 8/1/16.  Agreement to abide by tenant rules.
Exhibit #14 Tenant Handbook - signed by DE.  Re:  Inspections performed periodically, care of apartment, pet policy, etc.  Exhibits 13 and 14 - admitted and received.

Exhibit #15 - Pet Registration Form - Agreement to abide by rules - signed by DE.  No fences, chains, etc.  Immediately clean pet droppings outside on property, disabilities - not exempt from pet policies.  If rules violated and ask for pet removal, must remove or be evicted.  Exhibit admitted and received.  Witness states problems stared when dog moved in 2018 - feces in yard, multiple piles, not picked up.  She told DE of concerns and to pick up feces, DE unable to comply.
Exhibit #16 - Letter from DE - requests to allow her to clean up after 9:00 AM .  Request allowed.  Exhibit admitted and received.
Exhibit #17 - Letter from PL to DE.   Will allow DE to remove feces after 9:00 AM.  Occasions when feces not picked up after 9:00 AM.  Exhibit admitted and received.
Exhibit #18 - Annual Inspection Notice 6/9/21.  Precautions made for Covid - masks, social distancing, etc. .  Exhibit admitted and received.
Exhibit #19 - Email to PL from DE - 6/8/21 - Refusal to inspections.  Exhibit admitted and received.

Exhibit #20 - Email to PL from DE 6/18/21 .  Exhibit admitted and received.  Exhibit #21 - Notice to Vacate - 5 day notice to DE to remove pet re: violations and annual inspections.  Need to comply.  Exhibits admitted and received.
Exhibit #22 - Email to PL's Attorney from DE 6/24/21.  Exhibit admitted and received.
Exhibit #23 - Email to PL's Attorney from DE 6/28/21. Exhibit admitted and received.
Exhibit #24 - Email from PL's Attorney to DE - re annual inspection.   Annual inspection never conducted.  Exhibit admitted and received.  DE's unit is in apartment complex - shared yard.

Cross by Kathleen McBrair - DE moved from Port Wing unit to Iron River unit because of mold issue.  Does not know drain pipe installed.  Aware of ADA.  Not aware emotional support animals and medical therapy animals not considered pets.  Made accomodations for DE to pick up feces after 9:00 AM.  Aware of DE's medical issues.
Exhibit #25 - Photos of Bond St. property.    Witness aware of Fair Housing Act - made reasonable accomodations after 9:00 AM.
Redirect by Attorney Linda Colman:  Exhibit #17 - Housing Authority willing to allow 9:00 AM p/u time.  Reasonable accomodatons does not mean every/any accomodation requested by tenant.

Ellyn Conhartoski sworn in.  Direct by Kathleen McBriar - She is a licensed counselor at NorthLakes in Iron River with Masters of Science.  Working with DE since 5/20/21 after previous counselor resigned.  Describes DE's diagnosis - PTSD, etc.
Cross by Attorney Linda Coleman:  Difficult for DE to walk dog - triggers anxiety.

Redirect by Kathleen McBriar:  Been told by DE that dog is not outside for long periods.    Judge questions witness:  Previous medical provider at her office sent letter to Housing re: emotional support dog - 2017.

Judge: Adjourns Court Trial to October 15, 2021 at 1:00 PM - 3:00 PM.09-30-2021Exhibit
